begin_memory_text: She started off by asking for my name, and then introducing herself when i asked for her name. She asked where I was calling from and I told her, and I asked where she was calling from and she said LA. Then somehow we/I started talking about school
middle_memory_text: We talked about what got us each into our respective professions, and about my internships for school. We also talked about politics and what this year has been like for us each
end_memory_text: The topic shifted mainly to relationships, and I talked about my girlfriend and my conversation partner asked about how we met, what my girlfriend is like, if we want kids, etc. I also asked her if she wants additional children in the future
rest_of_day_open: I see it being filled with lots of school work that I've really been avoiding doing. I think everything will be ok because it always is. I have something exciting to look forward to this weekend, so I anticipate Saturday being a really fun and lighthearted day. Sunday I need to do a school project with someone, so lord knows how that will go. So things will be busy but they'll be good and meaningful.
critical_positive: My partner asked really good questions that required some depth in answers. She didn't ask me anything that could realistically be answered in one or two words, so that forced us to have a conversation. I felt that I took up more of the space though which I feel kind of bad about, but she seemed ok about it so it's all positive vibes here.
critical_negative: I think some of the questions she asked about me wanting kids in the future or when I anticipate moving in with my girlfriend took me a little off guard. It didn't bother me too much, but those are topics I haven't thought too much about yet. So being surprised by some of the content she asked about, but that was really it.

begin_memory_text: We talked about where we live. We also talked about our jobs. She is in school to become a social worker. We talked about why she wants to be a social worker.
middle_memory_text: We talked about COVID and our families. She is in a relationship. Her mom has breast cancer and has had to go in for treatment during the pandemic. We also talked about her animals and her dog.
end_memory_text: We talked more about her girlfriend. Her girlfriend loves animals too, and she adopts animals with problems. We discussed if she wants kids and when she wants them. We also talked about my son.
rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week going very well. I will continue to homeschool my son. I will also get to play with him. On the weekend, my son and I will get to spend time with my mom, which we enjoy. I will also work for DoorDash this weekend to make some extra money.
critical_positive: My partner was extremely friendly and very easy to talk to. She seemed like such a kind and intelligent person! She helped keep the conversation going. We also had a lot in common. She is somewhat close to my age. We both love animals, so I feel like we had a lot to talk about.
critical_negative: I felt like my awkwardness made the conversation harder than it should have been. I think maybe I asked too many questions and shared too much about my life. I feel like I may have made her feel uncomfortable when I shared more personal things. I am also not good at keeping a conversation going.
